headline: Prologis (PLD) Profit Margin Falls to 35.2%, Pressures Bullish Growth Narratives
summary: Prologis (PLD) reported a net profit margin of 35.2%, down from last year’s 37.4%, with annualized earnings growth averaging 12.2% over the past five years but slowing to just 4% this year. headline: Prologis Raises Outlook as Warehouse Leasing Picks Up
summary: The world’s largest owner of industrial real estate says companies are ramping up their warehouse-leasing decisions after three years of slow demand.  San Francisco-based  Prologis  on Wednesday said its revenue in the third quarter grew to $2.21 billion, up about 9% from $2.04 billion in the same quarter last year.  “Demand has clearly turned a corner,” said  Chris Caton,  managing director of global strategy and analytics at Prologis, on a call with investors Wednesday.

headline: Prologis Beats Estimates, Looks to AI Data Centers
summary: Real estate investment trust Prologis saw its shares rally Wednesday after the company reported better than expected earnings and the expected pursuit of data center opportunities. Incoming CEO Dan Letter believes the marketplace to be in the midst of a "classic real estate cycle right now," with big, well-capitalized customers leading the way. He joined Carol Massar and David Gura on 'Bloomberg Businessweek Daily' to break down the company's direction and macro economic trends.
